ing the negative one into a correction of the positive one). Like pseudo-Denys, the Eastern Church remarks the <a href="/wiki/Antinomy" title="Antinomy">antinomy</a> between the two ways of talking about God and acknowledges the superiority of apophatism. Cf. Vladimir Lossky, op. cit., p. 55, <a href="/wiki/Dumitru_St%C4%83niloae" title="Dumitru Stăniloae">Dumitru Stăniloae</a>, op. cit., pp. 261–262.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="languageicon">(in Romanian)</span> <a href="/wiki/Vladimir_Lossky" title="Vladimir Lossky">Vladimir Lossky</a>, <i>Teologia mistică a Bisericii de Răsărit</i> (<i>The Mystical Theology of the Eastern Church</i>), translation from <a href="/wiki/French_language" title="French language">French</a>, Anastasia Ed., <a href="/wiki/Bucharest" title="Bucharest">Bucharest</a>, 1993, pp. 36–37, 47–48, 55, 71. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>\xa0<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/973-95777-3-3" title="Special:BookSources/973-95777-3-3">973-95777-3-3</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Vision of God by <a href="/wiki/Vladimir_Lossky" title="Vladimir Lossky">Vladimir Lossky</a> SVS Press, 1997. (<a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>\xa0<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-913836-19-2" title="Special:BookSources/0-913836-19-2">0-913836-19-2</a>)</span>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="languageicon">(in Romanian)</span> <a href="/wiki/Dumitru_St%C4%83niloae" title="Dumitru Stăniloae">Fr. Dumitru Stăniloae</a>, <i>Ascetica şi mistica Biserici Ortodoxe</i> (<i>Ascetics and Mystics of the Eastern Orthodox Chu